def _normalize(value):
    return str(value).lower().replace("-", "_").replace(" ", "_")


def _special_doc(prefix, section, title, domain, act_name, focus, consequence, related, case_law, procedure):
    return {
        "id": f"{prefix}_{_normalize(section)}",
        "title": f"{act_name} - {title}",
        "section": f"Section {section}" if section[0].isdigit() else section,
        "domain": domain,
        "content": f"""{act_name} entry {section} deals with {title.lower()}. {focus} Many of these enactments are sector-specific but they share a common pattern: they create specialised rights, specialised forums or procedures, and a strong need for documentary, digital, or institutional compliance evidence. They are therefore particularly useful in practical legal AI applications because legal outcomes often turn on timelines, notices, records, and statutory preconditions rather than on broad abstract principles alone.

Penalty, liability, or remedial consequence: {consequence} Closely related concepts include {related}. Depending on the statute, proceedings may begin before a commission, special court, adjudicating officer, magistrate, labour authority, or internal committee. Lawyers also examine limitation, jurisdiction, vicarious liability, procedural safeguards, and whether a civil, criminal, or hybrid remedy has been triggered by the same facts.

Important interpretive points and case law: {case_law} In practice, {procedure}. This makes the {act_name} provision valuable for understanding not only the legal rule but also the compliance culture, enforcement pathway, and evidentiary demands of Indian special statutes.""",
    }


