    _special_doc(prefix='pocso', section='3', title='Penetrative Sexual Assault', domain='Criminal', act_name='POCSO Act, 2012', focus='This provision belongs to the Protection of Children from Sexual Offences Act, 2012, a child-centric criminal statute designed to address sexual abuse, exploitation, pornography, and procedural vulnerabilities of child victims.', consequence='The law creates stringent offences, child-friendly procedures, mandatory reporting, special courts, and presumptions that significantly shape prosecution strategy. Punishment is severe and rises sharply for aggravated conduct, repeated assault, or exploitative use of a child in pornography.', related='Special Court procedure, child-friendly evidence, medical examination, mandatory reporting, age determination, and overlap with IPC and Juvenile Justice law', case_law='Courts emphasise that consent of a minor is legally irrelevant, that child testimony can sustain conviction if credible, and that statutory presumptions must still be applied with fairness and proof of foundational facts.', procedure='cases require prompt protection of the child, age proof, medical support where relevant, careful recording of statements, in camera proceedings, and avoidance of secondary victimisation'),
