    _special_doc(prefix='posh', section='Definitions', title='Definitions and Scope of Workplace Sexual Harassment', domain='Labour', act_name='POSH Act, 2013', focus='This provision belongs to the Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace (Prevention, Prohibition and Redressal) Act, 2013, which creates a preventive and remedial framework for safe workplaces.', consequence='The law obliges employers to prevent, prohibit, and redress workplace sexual harassment through complaint committees, inquiry procedure, interim relief, confidentiality, and action recommendations. Non-compliance can attract penalties and affect licensing or reputation.', related='Vishaka principles, service rules, disciplinary procedure, labour compliance, and confidentiality requirements', case_law='Courts and tribunals treat the Act as a workplace safety and equality law, not merely a disciplinary formality. Proper constitution of ICC and fair inquiry are recurring issues.', procedure='employers must publish policy, train staff, constitute committees correctly, receive complaints within time or with extension where justified, and issue action decisions based on inquiry findings'),
